{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 4a, b shows that the diffusivity of CAPs behaves oppositely in the square and triangular lattices with the same area fraction.",
    "For instance, at high l p (≳100), CAPs diffuse faster in a dense square lattice than in free space (i.e., Ψ > 0) when r ≈ 2,4, but less mobile (Ψ < 0) at r ≈ 1,3,5 (Fig. 4a).",
    "By contrast, D eff > D when r ≈ 1,3,5 and < D when r ≈ 2,4 in the triangular lattice (Fig. 4b).",
    "The oscillatory behavior of Ψ with respect to r persists up to r ≈ 5, beyond which Ψ becomes insensitive to r (Fig. 4c).",
    "This chirality-sensitive behavior of diffusivity also diminishes for small l p at which active particles quickly lose their directionality (Fig. 4d)."
  ]
}